        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Telegram forum-topic subagent completion delivery",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Make native sub-agent completion an internal parent/requester handoff instead of forcing message-tool delivery or retrying for message-tool evidence.\n- Reduce `/subagents` to visibility only (`list`, `info`, `log`) and remove manual spawn/send/steer/kill slash-command paths.\n- Narrow the model-facing `subagents` tool to `list`, update prompts/docs/snapshots, and keep legacy replay safety for historical kill/steer tool events.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Telegram/forum-topic sub-agent completion no longer fails only because the parent/announce handoff did not call the message tool.\nReal environment tested: focused local Vitest shards plus Blacksmith Testbox `pnpm check:changed`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm test src/agents/subagent-announce-delivery.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/commands-subagents-routing.test.ts src/agents/tools/subagents-tool.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/slash-command-executor.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/slash-commands.node.test.ts`; `pnpm test src/agents/tool-mutation.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-subscribe.handlers.tools.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.subagents.scope.test.ts src/agents/tools/subagents-tool.test.ts src/agents/system-prompt.test.ts`; `pnpm check:changed`; `autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`.\nEvidence after fix: focused tests passed locally; Blacksmith Testbox `tbx_01ksa7yp14chxb1kknnk08wwrg` passed `pnpm check:changed`; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: sub-agent completions are accepted through the parent handoff, `/subagents` and the `subagents` tool expose status-only behavior, and removed control/spawn command paths are gone from docs, prompts, registry, UI, and snapshots.\nWhat was not tested: a live Telegram forum-topic run was not repeated in this pass.\n\nFixes #85070\n",
